---
import CaseStudy from '../../layouts/CaseStudy.astro';
---
<CaseStudy slug="scandalous">
  <Fragment slot="meta">
    <div class="cs-meta-card">
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Client</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Scandalous (SC)</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Duration</div><div class="cs-meta-value">2017 – present</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Role</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Brand &amp; GTM lead</div></div>
      <div class="cs-meta-row"><div class="cs-meta-label">Industry</div><div class="cs-meta-value">Regulated cannabis</div></div>
    </div>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="section">
    <div class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">$500K+</div><div class="stat-label">Raised through investor brand system</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">11–13</div><div class="stat-label">SKUs deployed across 5 states</div></div>
      <div class="stat-box"><div class="stat-num">9 yrs</div><div class="stat-label">Active client relationship</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Context · Action · Result</div>
    <div class="car-grid">
      <div class="car-sidebar">
        <div class="car-step active" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-1')"><div class="car-step-label">01 · Context</div><div class="car-step-title">The situation</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-2')"><div class="car-step-label">02 · Action</div><div class="car-step-title">What I built</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-3')"><div class="car-step-label">03 · Result</div><div class="car-step-title">What it produced</div></div>
        <div class="car-step" onclick="switchCar(this,'car-sc-4')"><div class="car-step-label">04 · Ongoing</div><div class="car-step-title">Where it stands now</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div id="car-sc-1" class="car-content">
          <div class="car-content-label">01 · Context</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">A regulated cannabis brand entering multiple state markets with no visual identity, no investor materials, and no production infrastructure.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Scandalous came in as a cannabis brand with strong product conviction and zero brand scaffolding. The challenge was building a visual system and market presence that could survive multi-state regulatory review, attract wholesale and licensing partners, and raise institutional capital — simultaneously.<br><br>Regulated consumer packaging is unforgiving: every state has different labeling requirements, warning language, sizing constraints, and compliance checkpoints. The brand had to flex across those requirements without losing visual coherence.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-2" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">02 · Action</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Built the full brand system, packaging architecture, and investor-facing materials from scratch.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Developed brand identity, typography, color system, and voice. Designed 11–13 SKUs of packaging across WA, OR, CA, IL, and NY — each state-compliant while maintaining visual brand coherence. Built investor decks, pitch materials, and a website that raised $500K+.<br><br>Developed the licensing and distribution pitch framework used to initiate partnerships across five states, including the active NY/Brooklyn expansion.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-3" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">03 · Result</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">$500K+ raised. Multi-state operations established. Anchor retainer relationship sustained for nine years.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">The brand system I built directly supported $500K+ in investor funding. 11–13 SKUs deployed across five regulated state markets. A consistent visual identity maintained across all compliance requirements. Six additional SKUs currently in the active pipeline.</div>
        </div>
        <div id="car-sc-4" class="car-content" style="display:none">
          <div class="car-content-label">04 · Ongoing</div>
          <div class="car-content-title">Nine-year client relationship, active expansion into New York.</div>
          <div class="car-content-body">Scandalous remains the anchor retainer for THIS (~$15K/yr). NY/Brooklyn licensing partnership is an active warm intro. Six SKUs in development pipeline. The relationship has sustained through every phase of THIS — from side consultancy through full-time primary business.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="section">
    <div class="section-label">Selected deliverables</div>
    <div class="asset-grid">
      <div class="asset-thumb">[Packaging — SKU lineup]</div>
      <div class="asset-thumb">[Investor deck — cover]</div>
      <div class="asset-thumb">[Brand identity — logo]</div>
      <div class="asset-thumb">[State compliance label]</div>
      <div class="asset-thumb">[Website / landing page]</div>
      <div class="asset-thumb">[Campaign asset]</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</CaseStudy>
